# shadcn/ui

> shadcn/ui is a collection of beautifully-designed, accessible components and a code distribution platform. It is built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Radix UI primitives. It supports multiple frameworks including Next.js, Vite, Remix, Astro, and more. Open Source. Open Code. AI-Ready. It also comes with a command-line tool to install and manage components and a registry system to publish and distribute code.

## When to Use This Rule

**Use this rule when:**

- ✅ **Working with existing shadcn/ui components** - Understanding component APIs, props, and usage patterns
- ✅ **Customizing shadcn/ui components** - Modifying components in `components/ui/` directory
- ✅ **Understanding configuration** - Reading `components.json` to understand component setup (do not modify unless necessary)
- ✅ **Understanding component structure** - Learning how shadcn/ui components are organized and composed
- ✅ **Accessibility concerns** - Understanding how Radix UI primitives provide accessibility features
- ✅ **Theming and styling** - Customizing component styles, variants, or design tokens
- ✅ **Form integration** - Using shadcn/ui components with React Hook Form or TanStack Form
- ✅ **Component composition** - Building complex UIs by composing shadcn/ui components

**Do NOT use this rule when:**

- ❌ **Installing new components** - ⚠️ **NEVER run `npx shadcn@latest add`** - All components have been customized and installation would overwrite customizations. Create new components manually or copy from existing ones.
- ❌ **Working with custom components** - For components in `components/custom/` or `components/form/` that aren't from shadcn/ui
- ❌ **Working with data tables** - Use `data-table.mdc` rule instead for TanStack Table patterns
- ❌ **Working with forms** - Use `tanstack-form.mdc` rule instead for form patterns
- ❌ **General UI patterns** - Use `styling-guide.mdc` for general styling and layout patterns
- ❌ **Feature structure** - Use `feature-structure.mdc` for organizing feature folders

## Quick Reference

**⚠️ CRITICAL: DO NOT Install New Components**

**NEVER run `npx shadcn@latest add`** - All components in `components/ui/` have been customized for this project. Installing new components would overwrite existing customizations.

**To add a new component:**

1. Manually create the component file in `components/ui/`
2. Reference the [shadcn/ui documentation](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs) for the component structure
3. Copy patterns from existing components in `components/ui/`
4. Customize as needed for project requirements

**Component Location:**

- Existing components: `components/ui/`
- Configuration: `components.json`
- Customizations: All components have been modified - edit files directly

**Key Principles:**

- Components are **copied into your project** (not installed as dependencies)
- Built on **Radix UI primitives** for accessibility
- Styled with **Tailwind CSS**
- All components have been **customized** - do not overwrite with CLI installations

